  "prompt": "How can I contact payment and settlement department of RBI?",
  "response": "To contact the **Payment and Settlement Department** of the Reserve Bank of India (RBI), you can use the following details:\n\n### **1. Postal Address:**\n```\nThe Chief General Manager,  \nPayment and Settlement Systems Department,  \nReserve Bank of India,  \nCentral Office,  \nShaheed Bhagat Singh Marg,  \nMumbai - 400001.\n```\n\n### **2. Email:**\nYou can send an email to the department at:\n```\npssdco@rbi.org.in\n```\n\n### **3. Phone:**\nFor general inquiries, you can contact the RBI's central office in Mumbai:\n```\n+91-22-22610100\n```\n\n### **4. Website:**\nVisit the RBI's official website for more information or to submit queries online:\n[RBI Payment and Settlement Systems](https://www.rbi.org.in/scripts/ps.aspx)\n\n### **5. Regional Offices:**\nIf your query is region-specific, you can also contact the nearest RBI regional office. The contact details for regional offices are available on the RBI website.\n\nWhen reaching out, ensure you provide clear details about your query or issue for a prompt response.",
